%20of%20those%20passengers%20died%20in%20the%20sinking%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fvideo%2F194837%2Foverview-Titanic%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBritannica%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20compared%20to%2075%25%20of%20third-class%20passengers%20who%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWilliams'%20escape%20from%20the%20Titanic%20may%20have%20inspired%20one%20of%20the%20most%20memorable%20scenes%20in%20the%201997%20movie%20about%20its%20sinking.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224903%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Titanic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a70a4edcdb354a98580d64%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223677%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Titanic%20departing%20Southampton%20on%20April%2010%2C%201912.%3Cp%3EPictures%20from%20History%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams%20later%20recounted%20the%20events%20of%20the%20ship's%20sinking%20in%20an%20unpublished%20memoir%2C%20which%20was%20passed%20on%20to%20his%20widow%20and%20his%20four%20children%20after%20his%20death%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mainlinemedianews.com%2F2012%2F04%2F12%2Fsinking-of-titanic-revisited-through-survivors-memoirs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMain%20Line%20Times%20%26amp%3B%20Suburban%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20sinking%2C%20he%20freed%20a%20passenger%20trapped%20in%20one%20of%20the%20cabins%20by%20breaking%20down%20a%20door%20that%20was%20stuck%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.si.com%2Ftennis%2F2015%2F04%2F20%2Fsi-vault-richard-williams-karl-behr-titanic-tennis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESports%20Illustrated%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20A%20member%20of%20staff%20then%20approached%20him%20and%20threatened%20to%20fine%20him%20for%20damaging%20the%20ship's%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20scene%20occurs%20in%20James%20Cameron's%20film%20%26quot%3BTitanic%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20Jack%20and%20Rose%20break%20down%20a%20door%20during%20their%20escape%20and%20are%20reprimanded%20for%20damaging%20White%20Star%20Line%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWilliams%20and%20his%20father%20stayed%20on%20the%20ship%20as%20long%20as%20possible%2C%20but%20ultimately%20his%20father%20did%20not%20survive.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224632%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Titanic%20lifeboat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a1c3376979d73718231ed7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223474%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESurvivors%20of%20the%20RMS%20Titanic%20in%20one%20of%20the%20ship's%20collapsible%20lifeboats%2C%20just%20before%20being%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20Carpathia%2C%20April%2015%2C%201912.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20men%20either%20jumped%20into%20the%20water%20or%20were%20washed%20overboard%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams%20later%20wrote%20in%20his%20memoir%2C%20parts%20of%20which%20were%20republished%20by%20Main%20Line%20Times%20%26amp%3B%20Suburban%20in%202012%2C%20that%20his%20father%20was%20crushed%20by%20a%20falling%20funnel%2C%20though%20his%20accounts%20differed%20slightly%20at%20different%20points%20in%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20escape%20the%20sinking%20boat%2C%20Williams%20removed%20his%20shoes%20and%20swam%20to%20a%20lifeboat%20about%20100%20yards%20away%2C%20although%20he%20recalled%20being%20weighed%20down%20by%20a%20fur%20coat%20he%20was%20wearing%20over%20his%20life%20jacket%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20reportedly%20held%20on%20to%20the%20lifeboat%20before%20climbing%20into%20it%2C%20and%20sat%20up%20to%20his%20knees%20in%20freezing%20water%20and%20waited%20to%20be%20rescued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20reported%20that%20%26quot%3Bonly%20about%20a%20dozen%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20passengers%20in%20Williams'%20lifeboat%20survived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWilliams%20sat%20in%20knee-deep%20water%20for%20several%20hours%20until%20he%20was%20brought%20aboard%20the%20Carpathia.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224369%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Titanic%20rescue%20ship%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e8b313229d6d93915510d87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223378%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20arrival%20of%20the%20Carpathia%20with%20rescued%20passengers%20of%20the%20Titanic%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Rinhart%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-titanic-passengers-getting-rescued-by-carpathia-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECarpathia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Williams%20was%20told%20by%20a%20doctor%20that%20his%20frostbitten%20legs%20would%20need%20to%20be%20amputated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20aspiring%20tennis%20professional%20refused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20refuse%20to%20give%20you%20permission%2C%26quot%3B%20Williams%20said%2C%20according%20to%20his%201968%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesmachine.nytimes.com%2Ftimesmachine%2F1968%2F06%2F04%2F91229551.pdf%3Fpdf_redirect%3Dtrue%26ip%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobituary%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20need%20these%20legs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetermined%20to%20save%20his%20legs%2C%20Williams%20walked%20around%20Carpathia's%20deck%20every%20two%20hours%2C%20eventually%20regaining%20sensation%20in%20his%20lower%20body%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWilliams%20went%20on%20to%20win%20multiple%20tennis%20titles%20and%20he%20won%20a%20gold%20medal%20at%20the%201924%20Paris%20Olympics.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224955%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20high-angle%20view%20of%20the%20opening%20ceremony%20at%20the%201924%20Summer%20Olympics%20in%20Paris%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a1c21fdcdb354a98576478%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223716%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20high-angle%20view%20of%20the%20opening%20ceremony%20at%20the%201924%20Summer%20Olympics%20in%20Paris.%3Cp%3EKeystone%2FHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20year%20that%20he%20survived%20the%20Titanic%20sinking%2C%20Williams%20won%20the%20US%20National%20Tennis%20Championships%20in%20mixed%20doubles%20alongside%20Mark%20K.%20Brown%20and%20ranked%20among%20the%20top%2010%20players%20in%20the%20world%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tennisfame.com%2Fhall-of-famers%2Finductees%2Frichard-norris-williams-2nd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Tennis%20Hall%20of%20Fame%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201916%2C%20he%20won%20the%20national%20title%20again%20and%20became%20the%20highest-ranked%20tennis%20player%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20his%20prowess%20on%20the%20tennis%20course%2C%20Williams%20also%20served%20in%20the%20US%20Army%20during%20World%20War%20I%20and%20was%20awarded%20two%20honors%2C%20the%20L%C3%A9gion%20d'Honneur%20and%20the%20Croix%20de%20Guerre%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Folympics.com%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fthe-titanic-survivor-who-won-olympic-gold-at-paris-1924%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOlympics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20war%2C%20Williams%20resumed%20his%20tennis%20career%2C%20and%20in%201920%2C%20he%20won%20a%20Wimbledon%20doubles%20title%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20his%20tennis%20career%20reached%20its%20peak%20at%20the%201924%20Paris%20Olympics%20when%20Williams%20won%20a%20mixed-doubles%20gold%20medal%20with%20his%20tennis%20partner%2C%20Hazel%20Hotchkiss%20Wightman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWilliams%20married%20twice%20and%20had%20four%20children%20after%20surviving%20the%20disaster.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%