instead%20to%20Indianapolis%20to%20speak%20at%20the%20historically%20Black%20Zeta%20Phi%20Beta%20sorority's%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20by%20accident%2C%20my%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarsour%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20not%20because%20she%20happens%20to%20be%20in%20Indianapolis.%20That%20is%20a%20strategic%20political%20calculation%2C%20because%20she%20knew%20%E2%80%94%20and%20her%20people%20knew%20%E2%80%94%20that%20you%20will%20not%20reach%20the%20White%20House%20if%20you%20frolic%20with%20war%20criminals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarsour's%20argument%20about%20Biden%20doesn't%20exactly%20hold%20water.%20It%20was%2C%20without%20question%2C%20Biden's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happened-biden-trump-debate-takeaways-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisastrous%20debate%20performance%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20forced%20him%20from%20the%20race%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-democrats-capitol-hill-paralysis-joe-biden-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree%20painful%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Democratic%20hand-wringing%20about%20the%20issue.%20Until%20the%20debate%20made%20questions%20about%20his%20age%20unavoidable%2C%20it%20was%20Biden's%20staunch%20support%20for%20Israel%20that%20seemed%20to%20pose%20the%20greatest%20threat%20to%20his%20candidacy.%20But%20it%20was%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Focasio-cortez-joe-biden-drop-out-criticism-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprogressive%20lawmakers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who've%20generally%20been%20the%20most%20outspoken%20about%20the%20destruction%20in%20Gaza%2C%20who%20chose%20to%20remain%20behind%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Sarsour's%20observation%20about%20Harris's%20absence%2C%20whatever%20the%20White%20House%20may%20say%20about%20scheduling%2C%20was%20shared%20by%20progressive%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20who%20would%20like%20to%20see%20the%20United%20States%20take%20a%20different%20approach%20toward%20Israel%20%E2%80%94%20and%20who%20are%20openly%20pining%20for%20Harris%20to%20break%20with%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20pretty%20big%20symbolic%20statement%2C%26quot%3B%20Rep.%20Ro%20Khanna%20told%20me%2C%20referring%20to%20Harris's%20absence.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20she%20has%20an%20opportunity%20to%20have%20a%20clean%20break%20from%20the%20administration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22With%20Harris%20absent%2C%20Sen.%20Ben%20Cardin%20of%20Maryland%20took%20her%20place.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a16574fb2b6bedb05a4a24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWith%20Harris%20absent%2C%20Sen.%20Ben%20Cardin%20of%20Maryland%20took%20her%20place.%3Cp%3EKent%20Nishimura%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20California%20Democrat%20argued%20that%20Harris%20should%20look%20toward%20the%20example%20of%20Vice%20President%20Hubert%20Humphrey.%20After%20President%20Lyndon%20B.%20Johnson%20withdrew%20from%20the%201968%20presidential%20race%20amid%20critics%20of%20his%20handling%20of%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20Humphrey%20entered%20the%20race%2C%20eventually%20calling%20for%20peace%20talks.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20Humphrey%20did%20that%2C%20his%20poll%20numbers%20skyrocketed%2C%26quot%3B%20Khanna%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20he%20almost%20won.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b61cfe17-add1-44a6-8b3c-877427338a83%5C%22%3E'A%20very%20tenuous%20feeling'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Netanyahu's%20speech%20on%20Wednesday%20was%20any%20indication%2C%20there's%20plenty%20of%20wiggle%20room%20for%20Harris%20to%20pursue%20a%20less%20deferential%20approach%20to%20Israel%20than%20Biden.%20Only%20about%20half%20of%20House%20and%20Senate%20Democrats%20even%20showed%20up%20for%20the%20speech.%20Dozens%20of%20progressives%20issued%20statements%20affirming%20that%20they%20were%20boycotting%20the%20speech%2C%20engaged%20in%20other%20events%2C%20or%20like%20Harris%2C%20simply%20came%20up%20with%20convenient%20scheduling%20conflicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20Netanyahu%20himself.%20He's%20long%20been%20a%20polarizing%20figure%20in%20American%20politics%2C%20generally%20enjoying%20closer%20relationships%20with%20Republicans%20than%20Democrats.%20The%20last%20time%20he%20addressed%20Congress%20in%202015%20%E2%80%94%20where%20he%20railed%20against%20then-President%20Barack%20Obama's%20nuclear%20deal%20with%20Iran%20%E2%80%94%20dozens%20of%20Democrats%20also%20skipped%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20don't%20agree%20with%20his%20policies%20and%20who%20he%20is.%20He's%20literally%20the%20Trump%20of%20Israel%2C%26quot%3B%20Rep.%20Maxwell%20Frost%20of%20Florida%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BHe%20wants%20Trump%20to%20win.%20He%20wants%20to%20undermine%20the%20President%20and%20the%20Vice%20President.%20%5BBoycotting%5D%20makes%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%20to%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetanyahu%20is%20also%20a%20controversial%20figure%20at%20home%2C%20facing%20criticism%20for%20failing%20to%20stop%20the%20October%207%20Hamas%20attacks%20and%20widespread%20protests%20last%20summer%20over%20his%20attempted%20judicial%20reform.%20Rep.%20Becca%20Balint%20of%20Vermont%2C%20a%20progressive%20Jewish%20Democrat%2C%20told%20me%20she%20would%20be%20boycotting%20the%20speech%20in%20part%20because%20her%20friends%20in%20Israel%20felt%20%26quot%3Blet%20down%20by%20Netanyahu.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20giving%20him%20this%20platform%20right%20now%20is%20the%20absolute%20wrong%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Balint%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20should%20be%20spending%20every%20waking%20moment%20trying%20to%20secure%20the%20release%20of%20the%20hostages%20and%20bringing%20an%20end%20to%20this%20war.%20This%20feels%20like%20just%20a%20way%20for%20him%20to%20further%20his%20own%20political%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20much%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20speech%20was%20about%20topics%20that%20garner%20bipartisan%20sympathy%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20Iran%20and%20the%20ongoing%20efforts%20to%20rescue%20Israeli%20hostages%20in%20Gaza%20%E2%80%94%20there%20were%20also%20aspects%20of%20the%20speech%20that%20were%20clearly%20aimed%20at%20ginning%20up%20the%20majority-Republican%20audience%20that%20showed%20up%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20these%20protestors%20hold%20up%20signs%20proclaiming%20'Gays%20for%20Gaza%2C'%26quot%3B%20Netanyahu%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20might%20as%20well%20hold%20up%20signs%20saying%20'Chickens%20for%20KFC.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20speech%20proceeded%20without%20any%20vocal%20disturbances.%20Rep.%20Rashida%20Tlaib%2C%20the%20sole%20Palestinian%20American%20member%20of%20Congress%2C%20held%20up%20a%20sign%20that%20blared%20%26quot%3BWar%20Criminal.%26quot%3B%20Afterward%2C%20former%20House%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FSpeakerPelosi%2Fstatus%2F1816208313572364356%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20speech%20was%20%26quot%3Bby%20far%20the%20worst%20presentation%20of%20any%20foreign%20dignitary%26quot%3B%20invited%20to%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rep.%20Rashida%20Tlaib%20of%20Michigan%20holds%20up%20a%20%26quot%3BWar%20Criminal%26quot%3B%20sign%20during%20Netanyahu's%20address.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a164ed2d66759f66fe02a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERep.%20Rashida%20Tlaib%20of%20Michigan%20holds%20up%20a%20%26quot%3BWar%20Criminal%26quot%3B%20sign%20during%20Netanyahu's%20address.%3Cp%3EAnna%20Moneymaker%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20it%20remains%20unclear%20whether%20Harris's%20approach%20to%20the%20conflict%20would%20differ%20from%20Biden's.%20After%20all%2C%20she's%20his%20vice%20president%20and%20thus%20shares%20some%20degree%20of%20responsibility%20for%20the%20actions%20that%20progressives%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funcommitted-democrats-biden-gaza-israel-trump-blame-michigan-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Buncommitted%26quot%3B%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20protesting%20for%20nearly%20a%20year.%20Her%20meeting%20with%20Netanyahu%20on%20Thursday%20may%20provide%20some%20early%20indications%20of%20any%20potential%20policy%20differences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20very%20least%2C%20her%20rhetoric%20on%20the%20issue%20appears%20to%20be%20tougher%20than%20Biden's.%20In%20March%2C%20she%20became%20the%20first%20member%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20call%20for%20a%20cease-fire%2C%20though%20she%20was%20referring%20to%20a%20temporary%20one%20that%20was%20part%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-israel-gaza-aid-state-of-union-no-other-path-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebroader%20framework%3C%2Fa%3E%20proposed%20by%20the%20White%20House.%20She%20has%20generally%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F03%2F26%2Fkamala-harris-joe-biden-israel-00148955%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20willing%20to%20publicly%20criticize%3C%2Fa%3E%20Israel.%20And%20she%20has%20expressed%20more%20sympathy%20for%20pro-Palestinian%20protesters%20than%20Biden%20often%20has%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenation.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitics%2Fkamala-harris-interview-profile-excerpt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etelling%20The%20Nation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20those%20demonstrators%20are%20%26quot%3Bshowing%20exactly%20what%20the%20human%20emotion%20should%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20incredibly%20important%20right%20now%20that%20she%20distinguishes%20her