redient%20in%20rabbit%20pellets%20because%20it%20provides%20two%20key%20types%20of%20fiber%3A%20digestible%20and%20indigestible.%20Mayer%20says%20gut%20bacteria%20break%20down%20digestible%20fiber%20into%20nutrients%20that%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20bunnies%20hopping%26quot%3B%20while%20indigestible%20fiber%20acts%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bscratch%20factor%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20rabbit's%20digestive%20system%20to%20keep%20digestion%20moving.%20These%20pellets%20also%20contain%20probiotics%20to%20further%20support%20the%20beneficial%20bacteria%20in%20your%20rabbit's%20gut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20find%20this%20food%20at%20major%20retailers%20for%20around%20%241.11%20per%20pound%20(that's%20less%20than%20%2430%20for%20a%2025-pound%20bag)%2C%20or%20save%20even%20more%20by%20signing%20up%20for%20auto%20shipments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20for%20baby%20bunnies%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20for%20baby%20bunnies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20rabbit%20food%20for%20baby%20bunnies%20contains%20essential%20nutrients%20to%20support%20growth%20and%20development.%20Their%20food%20should%20contain%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.canr.msu.edu%2Fresources%2Frabbit_tracks_feeds_and_feeding%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%25%20to%2015%25%20protein%2C%202%25%20to%203.5%25%20fat%2C%20and%2020%25%20to%2027%25%20fiber%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Baby%20bunnies%20also%20need%20more%20calcium%20than%20adult%20rabbits.%20The%20experts%20I%20spoke%20with%20say%20the%20best%20commercial%20rabbit%20feeds%20for%20growing%20bunnies%2C%20such%20as%20nutritionist-formulated%20Oxbow%20Essentials%20Young%20Rabbit%20Food%2C%20achieve%20this%20balance%20using%20alfalfa%20hay%20as%20a%20top%20ingredient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalcium%20is%20important%20for%20strong%20bones%20and%20teeth%2C%20while%20protein%20builds%20strong%20muscles.%20Even%20though%20this%20baby%20bunny%20food%20contains%20less%20calcium%20than%20my%20top%20pick%20for%20adult%20rabbit%20food%2C%20feeding%20it%20alongside%20unlimited%20alfalfa%20hay%20ensures%20young%20bunnies%20have%20a%20consistent%20calcium%20source%20throughout%20the%20day.%20%26quot%3BAlfalfa%20hay%20has%20more%20protein%20and%20calcium%20for%20growth%20than%20other%20hay%20types%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bryant%2C%20which%20complements%20the%20food's%20balanced%20nutrient%20profile.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20Oxbow%20Essentials%20Young%20Rabbit%20Food%20is%20a%20great%20option.%20It's%20packed%20with%20essential%20nutrients%20to%20help%20your%20bunny%20grow%20strong%20and%20comes%20in%20various%20sizes%20to%20fit%20your%20needs.%20Plus%2C%20Oxbow%20is%20trusted%20by%20pet%20parents%20and%20veterinary%20professionals%2C%20yet%20this%20food%20is%20more%20affordable%20than%20other%20comparable%20recipes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20for%20seniors%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20for%20seniors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOxbow%20Senior%20Rabbit%20Food%20is%20the%20best%20rabbit%20food%20for%20senior%20bunnies%20due%20to%20its%20unique%20nutritional%20blend.%20It%20combines%20the%20digestive%20benefits%20of%20fiber-rich%20Timothy%20grass%20with%20protein%20and%20calcium-rich%20alfalfa%20hay.%20This%20targeted%20formula%20aids%20muscle%20and%20bone%20health%20without%20overloading%20senior%20bunnies%20with%20calcium.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERabbits%20have%20naturally%20light%20bones.%20While%20advantageous%20for%20agility%20at%20a%20young%20age%2C%20a%20rabbit's%20bones%20can%20become%20brittle%20and%20prone%20to%20injury%20as%20they%20reach%20their%20senior%20years%2C%20generally%20around%205%20or%206%20years%20old%2C%20depending%20on%20breed.%20Calcium%20helps%20support%20strong%20bones%2C%20but%20Mayer%20says%20too%20much%20can%20lead%20to%20bladder%20stones.%20Oxbow%20Essentials%20Senior%20Rabbit%20Food%20tackles%20this%20challenge%20by%20carefully%20balancing%20Timothy%20and%20alfalfa%20hay%2C%20providing%20the%20essential%20calcium%20for%20strong%20bones%20while%20reducing%20the%20risk%20of%20bladder%20stones.%20The%20extra%20protein%20in%20alfalfa%20hay%20helps%20build%20strong%20muscles.%C2%A0This%20food%20also%20includes%20antioxidants%2C%20which%20have%20shown%20promising%20results%20in%20reducing%20the%20risk%20of%20degenerative%20diseases%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsymbiosisonlinepublishing.com%2Fveterinary-sciences%2Fveterinary-sciences10.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliver%2C%20kidneys%2C%20and%20brain%20in%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20dogs%20and%20may%20provide%20the%20same%20benefits%20for%20rabbits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20hay%20for%20young%20rabbits%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20hay%20for%20young%20rabbits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlfalfa%20hay%20is%20the%20recommended%20hay%20type%20for%20young%20rabbits%20because%20it's%20much%20richer%20in%20nutrients%20like%20calcium%20and%20protein%20than%20other%20hays.%20Mayer%20says%20quality%20alfalfa%20hay%20is%20a%20darker%20green%20and%20a%20bit%20more%20leafy%20than%20other%20hay%20types.%20Small%20Pet%20Select%20Alfalfa%20Hay%20is%20a%20top%20choice%20among%20both%20rabbit%20parents%20and%20veterinarians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPraised%20for%20its%20freshness%20and%20quality%2C%20this%20alfalfa%20hay%20is%20a%20favorite%20among%20rabbit%20owners%2C%20with%20many%20reporting%20their%20rabbits%20prefer%20it%20over%20other%20brands.%20Depending%20on%20the%20harvest%20time%2C%20your%20hay%20might%20even%20include%20dried%20blossoms%2C%20a%20tasty%20treat%20that%20can%20trigger%20happy%20bunny%20zoomies%20(binkies).%20Bryant%20echoes%20these%20positive%20reviews%2C%20saying%20she%20recommends%20Small%20Pet%20Select's%20line%20of%20rabbit%20products%20as%20another%20high-quality%20choice%20for%20rabbit%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20brand%20consults%20with%20a%20veterinary%20nutritionist%20to%20ensure%20their%20hay%20and%20feeds%20meet%20rabbit%20nutritional%20needs.%20However%2C%20as%20rabbits%20mature%2C%20their%20dietary%20needs%20change.%20Alfalfa%20hay%20becomes%20more%20of%20a%20treat%20due%20to%20its%20high%20nutrients%2C%20so%20adult%20rabbits%20should%20transition%20to%20a%20different%20hay%20or%20grass%20like%20Timothy%2C%20orchard%2C%20or%20brome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20hay%20for%20adult%20rabbits%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20hay%20for%20adult%20rabbits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdult%20rabbits%20should%20always%20have%20access%20to%20hay.%20It's%20more%20than%20just%20food%20%E2%80%94%20it%20provides%20essential%20fiber%20for%20their%20digestive%20system%20and%20helps%20maintain%20healthy%20teeth.%20Rabbit%20teeth%20grow%20continuously%20(about%202%20millimeters%20a%20day)%2C%20and%20Smith%20says%20chewing%20hay%20helps%20prevent%20overgrowth.%20Experts%20recommend%20Timothy%20hay%20as%20the%20preferred%20choice%20for%20adult%20rabbits%2C%20although%20orchard%20hay%20and%20brome%20grass%20are%20also%20suitable%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHay%20is%20often%20harvested%20multiple%20times%20a%20year%2C%20and%20each%20harvest%20is%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bcutting.%26quot%3B%20The%20cutting%20can%20affect%20the%20hay's%20nutritional%20value%20as%20well%20as%20texture%20and%20taste.%20Small%20Pet%20Select%20offers%20pet%20parents%20the%20choice%20between%20first%2C%20second%2C%20and%20third%20cuttings.%20The%20third%20cutting%20is%20the%20richest%20and%20leafiest%20of%20all%2C%20while%20the%20first%20cutting%20has%20more%20robust%20stems.%20Most%20pet%20parents%20find%20that%20the%20second%20cutting%20is%20the%20sweet%20spot%20for%20their%20adult%20rabbits.%20If%20you're%20unsure%20which%20hay%20is%20right%20for%20your%20bunny%2C%20the%20company%20offers%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fshop.smallpetselect.com%2Fcollections%2Fhay-for-rabbits%2Fproducts%2Fsampler-hay-box%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esampler%20pack%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202nd%20and%203rd%20cutting%20Timothy%20hay%2C%20oat%20hay%2C%20and%20orchard%20hay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Small%20Pet%20Select%20Timothy%20Hay%20might%20have%20a%20slightly%20higher%20upfront%20cost%20than%20other%20hay%20options%2C%20pet%20parents%20report%20their%20rabbits%20devour%20every%20last%20bit.%20This%20reduces%20waste%20compared%20to%20other%20brands%2C%20potentially%20saving%20money%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20especially%20when%20buying%20in%20bulk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20for%20hay%20allergies%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20for%20hay%20allergies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHay%20allergies%20shouldn't%20stop%20you%20from%20enjoying%20the%20companionship%20of%20rabbits.%20Small%20Pet%20Select%20Orchard%20Hay%20provides%20a%20nutritious%20alternative%20to%20Timothy%20hay%20that's%20less%20likely%20to%20cause%20hay%20fever%20in%20people.%20Orchard%20hay%20is%20still%20packed%20with%20fiber%20yet%20has%20minimal%20amounts%20of%20protein%20and%20calcium%2C%20ideal%20for%20adult%20rabbits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frabbitresource.org%2Frabbit-help%2Frabbit-and-hay-allergies-what-to-do%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHouse%20Rabbit%20Resource%20Network%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allergies%20are%20the%20leading%20cause%20of%20rabbit%20surrenders.%20They%20say%20switching%20from%20Timothy%20hay%20to%20orchard%20hay%20may%20solve%20the%20issue%2C%20as%20orchard%20hay%20is%20naturally%20less%20dusty.%20The%20freshness%20of%20the%20hay%20matters%2C%20too.%20That's%20why%20it's%20best%20to%20purchase%20it%20from%20a%20trusted%20brand%20with%20positive%20reviews%2C%20such%20as%20Small%20Pet%20Select.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20optimal%20freshness%2C%20store%20your%20hay%20in%20a%20dry%20area.%20Smith%20recommends%20leaving%20the%20hay%20in%20the%20cardboard%20box%20it%20comes%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20to%20look%20for%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20rabbit%20food%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20my%20experts%20and%20in-depth%20research%2C%20when%20choosing%20the%20best%20rabbit%20food%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20keep%20the%20following%20factors%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuaranteed%20analysis%20and%20nutrient%20profiles%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20guaranteed%20analysis%20section%20is%20on%20every%20pet%20food%20label%2C%20and%20it%20lists%20the%20percentages%20of%20key%20nutrients%20in%20the%20recipe%2C%20including%20protein%2C%20fat%2C%20fiber%2C%20and%20calcium.%20Experts%20say%20rabbits'%20nutritional%20requirements%20change%20based%20on%20age%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20to%20purchase%20specific%20feeds%20and%20hay%20for%20young%2C%20adult%2C%20and%20senior%20rabbits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeaning%20(8%20weeks)%20to%204%20to%206%20months%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Bunnies%20need%20the%20most%20nutrients%20during%20this%20growth%20spurt.%20Their%20pellets%20should%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.canr.msu.edu%2Fresources%2Frabbit_tracks_feeds_and_feeding%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%25%20to%2015%25%20protein%2C%202%25%20to%203.5%25%20fat%2C%20and%2020%25%20to%2027%25%20fiber%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20contain%20more%20calcium%20than%20adult%20rabbit%20food.%20Baby%20bunnies%20should%20also%20have%20unlimited%20access%20to%20alfalfa%20hay.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdult%20rabbits%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Rabbits%20about%206%20months%20and%20older%20require%20more%20fiber%20(20%25%20to%2025%25)%20and%20less%20protein%20(12%25%20to%2014%25)%20and%20calcium%20(1%25)%20than%20growing%20kits.%20Their%20fat%20intake%20should%20be%20less%20than%203%25%2C%20Smith%20says.%20Adult%20rabbits%20should%20have%20unlimited%20access%20to%20Timothy%20hay%2C%20orchard%20hay%2C%20or%20oat%20hay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESenior%20rabbits%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Rabbits%20may%20reach%20senior%20status%20around%205%20or%206%2C%20depending%20on%20their%20breed%2C%20Mayer%20says.%20Consider%20transitioning%20to%20a%20senior%20diet%20that%20incorporates%20a%20combination%20of%20high-fiber%20Timothy%20hay%20and%20nutritious%20alfalfa%20hay%2C%20unless%20your%20senior%20rabbit%20is%20gaining%20too%20much%20weight.%20Then%20you%20want%20to%20feed%20Timothy%20hay%20and%20limit%20pellets%20further%2C%20Smith%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFeed%20type%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20are%20two%20main%20types%20of%20feed%20to%20consider%20for%20your%20rabbit.%20My%20experts%20only%20recommend%20feeding%20baby%2C%20adult%2C%20and%20senior%20rabbits%20pellet%20foods.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuesli%20and%20cereals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20have%20larger%20pieces%20of%20ingredients.%20The%20disadvantage%20of%20muesli%20and%20cereals%20is%20that%20rabbits%20can%20pick%20out%20their%20favorite%20ingredients%2C%20leaving%20behind%20important%20nutrients%20and%20leading%20to%20waste.%20The%20experts%20I%20interviewed%20do%20not%20recommend%20muesli%20and%20cereals%20for%20any%20bunny%2C%20regardless%20of%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPellets%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20are%20ground-up%20complete%20and%20balanced%20feed%20that's%20compressed%2C%20so%20your%20bunny%20gets%20complete%20nutrition%20in%20every%20bite.%20In%20addition%20to%20ensuring%20a%20balanced%20meal%2C%20pellets%20often%20minimize%20waste%20because%20rabbits%20can't%20pick%20out%20their%20favorite%20bits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERabbit%20should%20always%20have%20access%20to%20hay%2C%20Mayer%20says.%20This%20means%20you'll%20want%20to%20give%20your%20rabbit%20large%20handfuls%20of%20hay%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20evenings.%20It%20also%20means%20choosing%20pellet%20food%20with%20hay%20as%20the%20first%20ingredient.%20For%20young%20rabbits%2C%20opt%20for%20alfalfa-based%20pellets.%20Adult%20rabbits%20can%20have%20pellets%20made%20with%20Timothy%20or%20orchard%20hay.%20Depending%20on%20your%20senior%20rabbit's%20needs%2C%20they%20may%20benefit%20from%20a%20pellet%20with%20Timothy%20hay%20as%20the%20first%20ingredient%20and%20alfalfa%20potentially%20included%20farther%20down%20the%20ingredient%20list.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20experts%20recommend%20avoiding%20foods%20where%20the%20following%20ingredients%20appear%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20ingredient%20list%3A%20peas%2C%20beans%2C%20nuts%2C%20potatoes%2C%20seeds%2C%20and%20dried%20fruits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoybean%20hulls%20are%20an%20exception%2C%20Bryant%20says.%20They're%20the%20fibrous%20outer%20part%20of%20the%20soybean%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20bean%20itself%20that%20contains%20plant%20proteins.%20Molasses%20is%20also%20a%20typical%20ingredient%20in%20high-quality%20rabbit%20food%20diets.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20really%20good%20brands%20that%20use%20molasses%20as%20a%20binder%2C%20and%20to%20be%20honest%2C%20there's%20absolutely%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Mayer%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20selected%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20selected%20the%20best%20rabbit%20food%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20narrow%20down%20the%20best%20rabbit%20food%20among%20the%20many%20options%2C%20I%20focused%20on%20the%20following%20criteria%20and%20the%20guidance%20shared%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20to%20look%20for%26quot%3B%20section%20above.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExpert%20interviews%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20interviewed%20three%20experts%20about%20rabbits'%20nutritional%20needs.%20Dr.%20Joerg%20Mayer%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20small%20animal%20medicine%20and%20surgery%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvet.uga.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Georgia%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Susan%20Smith%2C%20PhD%2C%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funcnri.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20North%20Carolina%20Nutrition%20Research%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20author%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F341745584_Gastrointestinal_Physiology_and_Nutrition_of_Rabbits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGastrointestinal%20Physiology%20and%20Nutrition%20of%20Rabbits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20former%20head%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwisconsinhrs.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWisconsin%20House%20Rabbit%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Dr.%20Jana%20Bryant%20is%20the%20lead%20veterinarian%20and%20managing%20partner%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cityvet.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECityVet%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERabbit%20owner%20community%20boards%20and%20product%20reviews%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20visited%20forums%20and%20online%20rabbit%20communities%20such%20as%20Reddit's%20rabbit%20subgroup%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20common%20health%20and%20nutrition%20concerns%20as%20well%20as%20which%20foods%20and%20hay%20are%20popular%20among%20rabbit%20parents.%20I%20also%20read%20user%20reviews%20of%20each%20product%2C%20only%20recommending%20those%20with%20overwhelmingly%20positive%20feedback.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredient%20review%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Rabbits%20have%20different%20dietary%20needs%20at%20different%20ages.%20I%20selected%20foods%20formulated%20for%20rabbits%20at%20varying%20life%20stages%20following%20the%20nutritional%20and%20ingredient%20guidance%20provided%20by%20the%20experts%20I%20interviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuality%20control%20and%20brand%20reputation%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Choosing%20a%20pet%20food%20brand%20that%20employs%20or%20consults%20with%20veterinary%20nutritionists%20provides%20assurance%20that%20the%20food%20is%20formulated%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20your%20pet%20at%20each%20life%20stage.%20I%20also%20gave%20high%20marks%20to%20brands%20with%20strong%20commitments%20to%20research%20and%20development%2C%20often%20collaborating%20with%20universities%20to%20advance%20understanding%20of%20pet%20nutrition.%20Additionally%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20my%20picks%20are%20recommended%20by%20veterinarians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERabbit%20food%20FAQs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20food%20is%20best%20for%20rabbits%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20rabbit%20food%20is%20hay%2C%20which%20should%20comprise%20about%2095%25%20of%20their%20diet.%20The%20remaining%20portion%20of%20a%20rabbit's%20nutrition%20should%20come%20from%20a%20high-quality%20pellet%20rabbit%20food%20that%20includes%20hay%20as%20the%20first%20ingredient.%20The%20best%20food%20for%20individual%20rabbits%20depends%20on%20their%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20the%20highest%20quality%20rabbit%20food%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20adult%20rabbits%2C%20we%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20Timothy%20hay-based%20pellet%20that%20doesn't%20contain%20seeds%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryant%20says.%20Baby%20bunnies%20should%20eat%20an%20alfalfa%20hay-based%20pellet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20brand%20of%20food%20is%20best%20for%20rabbits%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20reputable%20brands%20make%20quality%20rabbit%20food.%20Mayer%20says%20%26quot%3Bthe%20vast%20majority%20of%20big%20names%20in%20the%20industry%20have%20done%20a%20really%20good%20job%20in%20consulting%20with%20the%20nutritionists.%20The%20last%20thing%20they%20want%20to%20do%20is%20cause%20harm%20to%20a%20rabbit.%26quot%3B%20Bryant%20recommends%20Oxbow%20and%20Small%20Pet%20Select%20as%20two%20such%20brands.%20She%20trusts%20their%20feed%20and%20hay%20offerings%20for%20her%20lop-eared%20bunnies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhich%20pellets%20are%20best%20for%20rabbits%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20pellets%20for%20rabbits%20have%20hay%20as%20the%20first%20ingredient.%20For%20young%20rabbits%2C%20opt%20for%20alfalfa-based%20pellets%2C%20such%20as%20Oxbow%20Essentials%20Young%20Rabbit%20Food.%20Adult%20rabbits%20can%20have%20pellets%20made%20with%20timothy%20or%20orchard%20hay.%20I%20recommend%20Timothy-based%20Oxbow%20Essentials%20Adult%20Rabbit%20Food%20because%20it's%20veterinary%20nutritionist-formulated%20and%20available%20at%20an%20affordable%20price.%20For%20senior%20rabbits%20that%20are%20not%20overweight%2C%20Mayer%20says%20a%20combination%20of%20Timothy%20and%20alfalfa%20hay%20can%20be%20beneficial.%20I%20recommend%20Oxbow%20Essentials%20Senior%20Rabbit%20Food%2C%20a%20pellet%20food%20with%20a%20balanced%20profile%20of%20Timothy%20and%20alfalfa%20hay%20for%20optimal%20digestion%2C%20bone%2C%20and%20muscle%20health.%20Even%20high-quality%20pellets%20should%20be%20fed%20in%20moderation%2C%20with%20most%20of%20a%20rabbit's%20nutrition%20coming%20from%20hay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20vegetables%20can%20bunnies%20eat%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERabbits%20can%20eat%20leafy%20vegetable%20salads%2C%20like%20lettuce%2C%20carrot%20tops%2C%20and%20herbs.%20However%2C%20salads%20should%20be%20given%20in%20moderation%20as%20treats.%20Smith%20says%20carrots%20are%20sugary%2C%20while%20Mayer%20warns%20that%20too%20much%20lettuce%20could%20cause%20diarrhea.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20food%20should%20rabbits%20not%20eat%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20choosing%20commercial%20food%2C%20be%20sure%20it%20doesn't%20list%20peas%2C%20beans%2C%20seeds%2C%20nuts%2C%20or%20dried%20fruits%20as%20the%20first%20ingredients.%20Instead%2C%20look%20for%20rabbit%20food%20with%20hay%20as%20the%20first%20ingredient.%20Smith%20says%20rabbits%20shouldn't%20eat%20starchy%20vegetables%20like%20squash%2C%20potatoes%2C%20and%20corn%20because%20they%20can%20cause%20serious%20digestive%20problems.%20While%20Mayer%20says%20wild%20rabbits%20will%20come%20across%20and%20eat%20an%20occasional%20seed%2C%20seed%20shouldn't%20make%20up%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20your%20rabbit's%20diet%20either.%3C%