ran%20Khan's%20regime%2C%20the%20ruling%20PML-N%20supremo's%20son-in-law%20claimed%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENawaz%2C%2074%2C%20had%20returned%20from%20London%20in%20October%20last%20year%20after%20spending%20four%20years%20in%20self-imposed%20exile%20on%20medical%20grounds.%20Upon%20his%20arrival%2C%20he%20was%20acquitted%20in%20all%20the%20cases%20he%20was%20facing%20including%20the%20Al-Azizia%20Mills%20corruption%20case%20in%20which%20he%20was%20serving%20a%20seven-year%20imprisonment%20before%20leaving%20for%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20had%20gone%20to%20London%20(in%202022)%20and%20touched%20the%20knees%20of%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20and%20requested%20him%20to%20come%20to%20Pakistan%20and%20save%20it%20from%20the%20destruction%20of%20(former%20prime%20minister)%20Imran%20Khan%2C%26quot%3B%20Capt%20Muhammad%20Safdar%20(retd.)%20while%20addressing%20party%20workers%20of%20the%20ruling%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N).%20He%20said%20when%20Nawaz%20returned%20to%20become%20prime%20minister%20for%20the%20fourth%20time%20then%20the%20powerful%20circles%20(a%20reference%20to%20the%20powerful%20military)%20decided%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20stop%20him%20from%20becoming%20the%20premier%20they%20ensured%20that%20Nawaz%20lost%20the%20election%20from%20NA-15%20Mansehra%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20and%20chided%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20Pakistan%20for%20manipulating%20the%20result%20of%20Nawaz%2C%20a%20three-time%20former%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20Nawaz%20had%20won%20Lahore's%20seat%20in%20the%20February%208%20general%20election%20which%20Khan's%20party%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20alleged%20that%20he%20had%20also%20lost%20this%20seat%20but%20the%20ECP%20declared%20him%20successful%20in%20the%20country's%20worst-ever%20rigged%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENawaz%20himself%20had%20admitted%20that%20he%20was%20a%20candidate%20to%20become%20premier%20but%20his%20party%