22%3A%22Consolidated%20revenue%20from%20operations%20in%20the%20quarter%20under%20review%20stood%20at%20Rs%201%2C804.47%20cr%20against%20Rs%201%2C663.97%20cr%20in%20the%20year-ago%20period%2C%20it%20added%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fjk-paper-q1-results-net-profit-declines-55-to-rs-140-79-cr-as-prices-fall-124072401127_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fjk-paper-q1-results-net-profit-declines-55-to-rs-140-79-cr-as-prices-fall-124072401127_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fjk-paper-q1-results-net-profit-declines-55-to-rs-140-79-cr-as-prices-fall-124072401127_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20Find%20Traces%20Of%20Water%20In%20Lunar%20Soil%20Brought%20By%20Change-5%20mission%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EChinese%20scientists%20studying%20the%20soil%20samples%20of%20the%20moon%20brought%20by%20the%20Chang'e-5%20mission%20found%20water%20molecules%20in%20lunar%20soil%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Chinese%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%20(CAS).%20The%20research%20-%20carried%20out%20jointly%20by%20researchers%20from%20the%20Beijing%20National%20Laboratory%20for%20Condensed%20Matter%20Physics%20and%20the%20Institute%20of%20Physics%20of%20CAS%20and%20other%20domestic%20research%20institutions%20-%20was%20published%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Nature%20Astronomy%20on%20July%2016%2C%20the%20Hong%20Kong-based%20South%20China%20Morning%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20lunar%20soil%20samples%20returned%20by%20the%20Chang'e-5%20mission%20in%202020%2C%20Chinese%20scientists%20have%20found%20a%20hydrated%20mineral%20%26quot%3Benriched%26quot%3B%20with%20molecular%20water%2C%20CAS%20said%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20India's%20Chandrayaan-1%20spacecraft%20detected%20signs%20of%20hydrated%20minerals%20in%20the%20form%20of%20oxygen%20and%20hydrogen%20molecules%20in%20sunlit%20areas%20of%20the%20moon.%20Among%20its%20suite%20of%20instruments%2C%20it%20carried%20NASA's%20Moon%20Mineralogy%20Mapper%20(M3)%2C%20an%20imaging%20spectrometer%20that%20helped%20confirm%20the%20discovery%20of%20water%20locked%20in%20minerals%20on%20the%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20NASA%20announced%20the%20discovery%20of%20water%20on%20the%20sunlit%20surface%20of%20the%20moon%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20airborne%20Stratospheric%20Observatory%20for%20Infrared%20Astronomy%2C%20which%20detected%20water%20molecules%20in%20the%20Clavius%20crater%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20craters%20visible%20from%20Earth%2C%20in%20the%20moon's%20southern%20hemisphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20lack%20of%20returned%20lunar%20samples%20from%20high%20latitude%20and%20polar%20regions%20means%20that%20%26quot%3Bneither%20the%20origin%20nor%20the%20actual%20chemical%20form%20of%20lunar%20hydrogen%20has%20been%20determined%26quot%3B%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Nature%20article.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Chinese%20scientists%20studying%20the%20lunar%20soil%20isolated%20more%20than%201%2C000%20mineral%20%26quot%3Bclasts%26quot%3B.%20The%20researchers%20said%20that%20among%20them%20was%20a%20platelike%20transparent%20crystal%2C%20dubbed%20%26quot%3Bunknown%20lunar%20mineral%26quot%3B%20(ULM-1)%2C%20that%20contained%20water%20molecules%2C%20the%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20ruled%20out%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20water-bearing%20mineral%20was%20contaminated%20by%20terrestrial%20sources%20or%20rocket%20exhaust.%20But%20one%20geochemist%20said%20he%20expected%20the%20team%20to%20find%20more%20evidence%20in%20their%20further%20study.%20%26quot%3BIf%20this%20water-bearing%20mineral%20is%20present%20in%20the%20lunar%20samples%2C%20more%20than%20one%20piece%20should%20be%20found%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20scientist%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20and%20was%20not%20associated%20with%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20returned%20lunar%20samples%20from%20high%20latitude%20and%20polar%20regions%20means%20that%20%26quot%3Bneither%20the%20origin%20nor%20the%20actual%20chemical%20form%20of%20lunar%20hydrogen%20has%20been%20determined%26quot%3B%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Nature%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chang'e-5%20China's%20first%20lunar%20sample-return%20mission%20sent%20back%20the%20first%20on-site%20evidence%20of%20water%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20moon%20in%202020.%3Cbr%3E%5CnMore%20discoveries%20were%20expected%20to%20follow%20with%20the%20return%20to%20Earth%20last%20month%20of%20China's%20Chang'e-6%20moon%20mission%20with%20up%20to%202kg%20of%20material%20scooped%20and%20drilled%20from%20the%20moon's%20oldest%20basin%20on%20the%20lunar%20far%20side.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%26quot%3BChina's%20Chang'e-5%20mission%20in%202020%20initiated%20a%20new%20phase%20of%20in-depth%20studies%20on%20lunar%20samples%20after%20a%2044-year%20hiatus%2C%20advancing%20our%20understanding%20of%20the%20moon's%20evolution%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Li%20Xianhua%2C%20an%20academician%20of%20the%20CAS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20prior%20to%20the%20Chang'e-6%20mission%2C%20all%20ten%20lunar%20sampling%20missions%20in%20human%20history%2C%20including%20the%20Chang'e-5%20mission%2C%20took%20place%20on%20the%20near%20side%20of%20the%20moon.%20%26quot%3BOur%20current%20knowledge%20of%20the%20moon%20primarily%20comes%20from%20research%20on%20samples%20collected%20from%20its%20near%20side%2C%20which%20does%20not%20represent%20a%20comprehensive%20scientific%20understanding%20of%20the%20whole%20moon%2C%26quot%3B%20Li%20told%20state-run%20Xinhua%20news%20agency.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%